<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Renting is on the rise among senior citizens amid a boom in demand for retirement living lets. </p>

<p>Specialist senior living properties to rent are set to jump by 160 per cent over five years, according to property consultancy Knight Frank. </p>

<p>On the increase: Specialist senior living properties to rent are set to jump by 160 per cent over five years</p>

<p>Lockdown is thought to have accelerated the trend towards later-life renting. </p>

<p>Retirement property firm Inspired Villages said it had seen a 'marked rise' in interest since March. </p>

<p>Chief executive Jamie Bunce said: 'The option to rent offers customers a chance to experience the benefits of village life.' </p>

<p>Tom Scaife, at Knight Frank, added: 'Renting in later years gives the flexibility to move around quicker and easier.'</p>
